race.comment: COOL MOON (1) is unlucky to still be a maiden hitting the top-four in all eight career outings to date and strikes a very winnable contest here. Drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley and gets some weight relief with the 2kg claim. Ticks plenty of boxes for a race like this. SHOWN THE DOOR (7) was well in the betting when facing the starter for the first time but just ran into a couple better on that occasion. Will have taken benefit from that hit-out and looms as the main danger. DEFIANT MISS (3) just missed the frame over this track and trip on debut and will have come on with that run now under the belt. Top-three candidate. EMPHATIQUE (10) may have suffered from the dreaded second-up syndrome last time out but go on the solid placing when resuming. Can bounce back with Wiggins on board. SWEEDISH QUEEN (8) looked handy winning a recent trial and should be kept very safe.
